The park groundskeeper has been fighting a losing battle against ash tunnel rats burrowing up from the Nightfall Catacombs beneath the city park. The root systems of the lavender beds and fountain borders have been disrupted repeatedly by their tunneling. Clear eight ash tunnel rats from the upper catacomb approaches beneath the park to give the groundskeeping team a chance to restore the planting schedule.
The groundskeeper's damage reports have dropped to zero for the first time this season. Replanting of the disturbed lavender beds is already underway, and the fountain borders have been cleared and re-edged. The park maintenance crew has filed a positive incident update with the Registry, noting that the catacomb boundary appears stable for the first time in several seasons.
